    "componentChoices": "The design leverages the existing design system components for consistency and efficiency. List items are used for settings entries, toggles for on/off actions, and text inputs for editable fields. The AppBar serves as top navigation, and a Bottom navigation bar provides access to other app sections. A tooltip component is used for detailed descriptions or help text.",
    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through section headings, color coding (e.g., green for personal info), toggle states, and the use of arrows to indicate navigation. The prominent placement of the 'Log out' button in the end emphasizes its importance.  The text styling uses Headline, Title, Body, and Caption sizes for clear visual prominence.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "Variants are carefully chosen to match the design system's components to the content's semantic meaning.  The 'list-item' component uses 'Trailing: Arrow' for editable settings, 'Trailing: Switch' for toggles, and 'Trailing: Info' for the Verified ID badge. Button variants are chosen for emphasis, type, and semantic state. For example, 'Delete Account' button will use 'Error' color to highlight destructive nature."
  }
}
